    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-08-01T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-08-01T20:00:00-05:00" n="389"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d389">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">897.2395/8–151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Indonesia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d389fn1">Repeated to Bangkok as telegram 277, to London as
                        748, to Colombo as 50, and to Singapore as 143.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-08-01T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 1, 1951—9 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>138. Colombo papers claim US official going Ceylon negot bulk purchase rubber
                    contract. Imply US willing consider 5 year term and six shilling price in return
                        <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> agreement embargo rubber Commie China.
                    Only factual basis these stories is US Govt asked whether <gloss
                        target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> interested rubber contract along lines Thai
                        <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> contracts. Absolutely not true more
                    favorable terms offered and <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> specifically
                    told approach made as friendly gesture and with no China angle. Inform Thai and
                        <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> govts soonest. Dept plans discuss with
                    Ceylon Amb Wash and will report discussion.</p>
                <p>If approached by press you shld deny knowledge negots or contract such as alleged
                    Colombo papers but shld indicate US always ready discuss proposals of fon govts.
                    Existence Thai <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> contracts still secret and
                    should not be communicated press or rubber trade any country, or to govts UK
                    Ceylon Malaya.</p>
                <p>This tel sent Djakarta, Bangkok, Colombo, London, Singapore.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
